                        "content": "The nurse is caring for a client receiving mannitol via intravenous (IV) infusion. A vial is sent from the pharmacy, and in preparing the medication the nurse notes that the vial contains crystals. What is the most appropriate nursing action?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "80db17ea97ed8fdcd1b6b9666390fca1",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Applying 应用",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nCrystals form in a mannitol solution if the solution is cooled, but they will quickly dissolve if the container is placed in warm water and then cooled to body temperature before administration. However, if crystals remain after the warming procedure, the medication would not be used and would need to be returned to the pharmacy. The nurse would not discard the medication. The medication is not initially returned to the pharmacy because it is not defective. Shaking the vial would not be done and will not dissolve the crystals.",
                        "id": "0d0313e742694326ad1cbdb97b8f21f1",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "9fffec9d6bbc48479efa61220b79e186",
                                "content": "Fat"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "ea35d690e64148cb9329fa6652cbccd0",
                                "content": "Starch"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
