                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client who is sedated. The client displays no response to voice, no response to physical stimuli, and no eye-opening response. Under which sedation level would the nurse categorize this response?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "c2472dbaf30269ec1d4a4af474a31869",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Understanding 理解",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe Richmond Agitation-Sedation Scale (RASS) is a standardized tool used to categorize sedation levels and assist with titrating sedation medications. The RASS scale categories range from unresponsive to combative. If the client displays no response to voice, no response to physical stimuli, and no eye-opening response, the response would be categorized as deep sedation.",
                        "id": "69b0e00d69a547c9960eeb7f6bda36bb",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
