                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "Propofol is being administered to induce sedation in a client who is intubated and is being mechanically ventilated. The nurse would monitor for which adverse effect during infusion of the medication?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPropofol is an anesthetic agent that is used to provide continuous sedation in a client receiving mechanical ventilation. Adverse effects include respiratory depression and cardiovascular depression. Itching, skin redness, and elevated triglyceride levels are possible side effects, not adverse effects.",
                        "id": "f790817eca2047f18e48240cd6a5dfd7",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "93c7745d0b47464db45e2c36528e1509",
                                "content": "Reduced ICP"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "a75cb0bd87b44379969f899cdcc71e5c",
                                "content": "Increased diuresis"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d7453bff789e47ca9ae57d5952ffd58a",
                                "content": "Increased osmotic pressure of glomerular filtrate"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "77f4fa9503e8452b9a2135c2103acd64",
                                "content": "Reduced tubular reabsorption of water and solutes"
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "3d223d5867f34efd9d5dd0aaf8e41a32",
                                "content": "Reabsorption of sodium and water in the loop of Henle"
                            }
                        ],
